attributedDescription.content:
I am in conversation with  Dr Marlain is an award Winning Arabic Speaking Consultant Obstetrician and Gynecologist at King’s, with extensive experience in Laparoscopic/Hysteroscopic surgeries. 

In this video, we discuss urinary incontinence. Many women suffer through this there isn't much conversation around it. The stigma around incontinence is vast and wide. The involuntary passing of urine while coughing, sneezing or laughing even happens due to incontinence but because there is not much awareness, women don't even address it to the Doctor out of embarrassment. 

Incontinence happens when the pelvic floor muscles are loose and stretched due to giving birth to a child. 
There are different ways to treat this and Doctor Marlain takes us through some of them and also sheds light upon many other things around Incontinence. 


If you want to know more, please drop your questions in the comments below

You can check Dr Marlain's channel here: 
   / @drmarlainmubarak...

attributedDescriptionBodyText.content:
I am in conversation with  Dr Marlain is an award Winning Arabic Speaking Consultant Obstetrician and Gynecologist at King’s, with extensive experience in Laparoscopic/Hysteroscopic surgeries. 

In this video, we discuss urinary incontinence. Many women suffer through this there isn't much conversation around it. The stigma around incontinence is vast and wide. The involuntary passing of urine while coughing, sneezing or laughing even happens due to incontinence but because there is not much awareness, women don't even address it to the Doctor out of embarrassment. 

Incontinence happens when the pelvic floor muscles are loose and stretched due to giving birth to a child. 
There are different ways to treat this and Doctor Marlain takes us through some of them and also sheds light upon many other things around Incontinence. 


If you want to know more, please drop your questions in the comments below

You can check Dr Marlain's channel here: 
   / @drmarlainmubarak...
